Package padsof

Class RegisteredUser

  • java.lang.Object
    • padsof.RegisteredUser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class RegisteredUser
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Author:
    David Cabornero and Alejandro Santorum This class allows us to create a new registered user. We can also save his data (nick, password, comments, credit card...) or modify this personal values.

    • Constructor Detail

      • RegisteredUser

        public RegisteredUser​(java.lang.String nick,
                      java.lang.String id,
                      java.lang.String password,
                      java.lang.String creditCard,
                      java.lang.String userChar)
               throws UserException
        This constructor allows us to create a new RegisteredUser
        Parameters:
        nick - The name of the user in the application
        id - ID (unique) of the user
        password - User's secret password
        creditCard - Credit card number of the user
        userChar - 'O' if the user is LANDLORD, 'D' if the user is RENTER, 'OD' if the user is both
        Throws:
        UserException - invalid user
